%description:
Deterministic MLDv1 host-behavior test (RFC 2710).

Tests all four host behaviors via Cmdenv log assertions with a fixed RNG seed:

HOST-01 (unsolicited Report on join):
  host1 and host2 join ff0e::1:2:3 via Mldv1's testMulticastGroup parameter,
  which calls multicastGroupJoined() directly during INITSTAGE_NETWORK_LAYER.
  This bypasses the UDP addMulticastAddressToInterface path (which calls
  assignAddress for IPv6 instead of joinMulticastGroup, thus not firing
  ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal). Mldv1 sends an unsolicited Multicast Listener
  Report immediately on the join.

HOST-03 (report suppression):
  Both hosts join the same group and both send unsolicited Reports at t=0.
  Because all nodes are on the SAME Ethernet segment (via EthernetHub), host2
  hears host1's Report while host2 is still in DELAYING_LISTENER state.
  host2 suppresses its own pending timer (cancelEvent, flag=false,
  state=IDLE_LISTENER). The test asserts the "received Multicast Listener
  Report" log line from host2, proving the suppression path was exercised.

HOST-02 (delayed Report on General Query):
  The router has sendTestQuery=true, which fires at t=2s and sends a General
  MLD Query (type=130, multicastAddress=::, maxRespDelay=1000ms) to ff02::1.
  All nodes on the shared Ethernet segment receive it. Hosts receive it via
  processMldMessage -> processQuery -> processGroupQuery. Idle Listeners
  transition to Delaying Listener and schedule uniform(0, 1s) delayed Reports.
  The test asserts the "received General Listener Query" log line from host1
  and then a subsequent "sending Multicast Listener Report".

HOST-04 (Done on leave):
  host1 has sendTestLeave=true, which fires at t=5s and calls multicastGroupLeft()
  directly for all joined groups. This bypasses the UDP leaveMulticastGroup path
  (NetworkInterface::changeMulticastGroupMembership is not implemented for IPv6).
  After the Query-driven Report (t~2..3s), host1's flag=true, so Done is sent to
  ff02::2 (ALL_ROUTERS_2).

Network: host1, host2, and router all connect to a shared EthernetHub, putting
them on the same Ethernet segment. Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns addresses.
All three nodes have hasMld=true. The router injects the test Query at t=2s.
RNG seed is fixed for reproducibility.

Note: the Mldv1 testMulticastGroup, sendTestQuery, and sendTestLeave parameters
are all default(false)/"" so they are inert in all production scenarios.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network MldHostBasicNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host1: StandardHost6;
        host2: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host1.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        host2.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = MldHostBasicNetwork
sim-time-limit = 10s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# Fix RNG seed for deterministic behavior of uniform(0, maxRespTime) in startHostTimer
seed-set = 0

eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# Enable MLD on all nodes
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
# Disable DAD for fast startup (no 1s+ delay before addresses are ready)
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# HOST-01/03: host1 and host2 both join ff0e::1:2:3 directly via testMulticastGroup.
# This calls multicastGroupJoined() during INITSTAGE_NETWORK_LAYER, bypassing the
# UDP assignAddress path that does not fire ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal for IPv6.
# On the shared Ethernet segment, each host's unsolicited Report is seen by the other,
# triggering report suppression (HOST-03).
**.host1.ipv6.mldv1.testMulticastGroup = "ff0e::1:2:3"
**.host2.ipv6.mldv1.testMulticastGroup = "ff0e::1:2:3"

# HOST-02: router sends one General MLD Query at t=2s (sendTestQuery=true).
# All nodes on the shared segment receive it; hosts transition Idle -> Delaying.
**.router.ipv6.mldv1.sendTestQuery = true

# HOST-04: host1 triggers multicastGroupLeft at t=5s via sendTestLeave=true.
# This bypasses the UDP leaveMulticastGroup path (not implemented for IPv6).
# After the Query-driven Report (t~2..3s), host1's flag=true -> Done sent to ff02::2.
**.host1.ipv6.mldv1.sendTestLeave = true

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-01: unsolicited Multicast Listener Report sent by host1 on join
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mldv1: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-03: report suppression -- host2 hears host1's Report for ff0e::1:2:3 while in DELAYING state
%# and cancels its own pending timer (both hosts are on the same Ethernet segment via hub)
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host2.ipv6.mldv1: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-02: router's General Query at t=2s is received by host1
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mldv1: Mldv1: received General Listener Query on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-02: after the General Query, host1 schedules and sends a delayed Report (within 1s)
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mldv1: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOST-04: Done sent to ff02::2 when host1 leaves at t=5s (flag=true after Query-driven Report)
%contains: stdout
MldHostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mldv1: Mldv1: sending Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1:2:3

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
